 to ensure clarity for anyone reviewing the information. Balancing these considerations seems crucial in providing a helpful response!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency, Docker image, environment variable, or system property is required before meaningful coverage is reachable for jakarta.activation:jakarta.activation-api:2.0.0. The javac failure is caused by generated tests using the old javax.activation namespace against the Jakarta 2.x artifact, whose classes are in jakarta.activation.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For version 2.0.0, generated tests must import and reflect on jakarta.activation.* classes, not javax.activation.*. Keep tests focused on API-jar-reachable behavior unless intentionally testing the separate implementation artifact.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The jakarta.activation-api artifact is API-oriented and has no transitive implementation dependency; some registry-backed APIs such as MailcapCommandMap or MimetypesFileTypeMap reference com.sun.activation.registries classes that live in the separate implementation artifact. Avoid making those implementation-backed paths the only coverage for this API coordinate unless the workflow deliberately adds and accepts that separate implementation dependency.\",\n    \"com.sun.activation:jakarta.activation:2.0.0 is already a separate library coordinate in this repository, so adding it here could conflate API-artifact coverage with implementation-artifact coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_085c4fcec8d8f355016a41a7d637ec8193aaa8136adbe211eb\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 742, "output": 788, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27130, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782687691517, "responseId"